      ------------------------------------------------
       OpenTelemetry Collector configuration example
      ------------------------------------------------


1. Overview
------------------------------------------------------------------------------

This directory contains a reference configuration file for running an
OpenTelemetry Collector alongside the OTel C wrapper test programs.  The
Collector receives telemetry data over multiple protocols and forwards it
to configured backends.


2. Configuration summary (config.yaml)
------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Extensions:

  health_check   Exposes the Collector health status endpoint.
  pprof          Go profiling endpoint on 127.0.0.1:1777.
  zpages         Debugging pages on 127.0.0.1:55679.

Receivers:

  otlp           Accepts OTLP data over gRPC (127.0.0.1:4317) and HTTP
                 (127.0.0.1:4318).  These are the primary endpoints used by the
                 OTel C wrapper library.
  prometheus     Scrapes the Collector's own metrics from 127.0.0.1:8888 every
                 10 seconds.
  jaeger         Accepts Jaeger traces over gRPC (14250), Thrift binary (6832),
                 Thrift compact (6831), and Thrift HTTP (14268).
  zipkin         Accepts Zipkin traces on 127.0.0.1:9411.

Processors:

  batch          Batches telemetry data before export using default settings.

Exporters:

  debug          Prints telemetry to the Collector's standard output with
                 detailed verbosity.
  otlphttp       Forwards data over OTLP/HTTP to a remote endpoint.  The
                 destination address in the file is an example and should be
                 changed to match your environment.

Pipelines:

  traces         Receives from otlp, jaeger, and zipkin; exports to debug and
                 otlphttp.
  metrics        Receives from otlp and prometheus; exports to debug.
  logs           Receives from otlp; exports to debug.

All receiver endpoints are bound to 127.0.0.1 to limit network exposure.
Change them to 0.0.0.0 if the Collector needs to accept remote connections.


3. Running the Collector
------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Download or install the OpenTelemetry Collector from:
  https://opentelemetry.io/docs/collector/installation/

Start the Collector with this configuration:

  % otelcol --config config.yaml

Then run the test program with its YAML configuration pointing to the OTLP
receiver endpoint (gRPC on port 4317 or HTTP on port 4318).
